@node "Descriptions" "Descriptions"
The main difference between SPin and MAXs normal file base is the
description. Basically this is how incorporates file_id.diz into MAXs file
base.

All file attributes are identical.

If the description is <60 chars then it's stored as normal.

If the description entered/file_id.diz extracted is >59 chars, then the
description within the file.data (file editor) will be

<SPin:DIz/filename.ext.file_id.diz

A problem exists with having seperate file_id's.  The problem is when a user
does a keyword search it would have to search each individual file_id.

SPin approaches this problem by storing all the file_id's in a seperate file

SPin:DIz/SPeedSEarch.DIzs

You may think this inefficient as the file_id is stored twice. But this is
the only good way of keeping file lists options identical to MAXs (ie.
Sorted/Reversed etc.)  It also allows you to add comments to file_ids without
these comments being "hit" in a keyword search.

See @{"Customisation" link "Customisation" 0} on how to speed up keyword searches.

Or jump back to @{"Main" link "Main" 0}                             
@endnode

