@node "Commercial" "Commercial version"
Future versions of SPin will not be Freeware, since Shareware never works
I've decided to make it a Commercially available piece of s/w

It should be ready by the end of August and will come in at around 15 UK
Pounds.

Note: It will NOT be a tweaked version of the freeware copy. Many new
features will be added, and certain parts totally re-written. Contact me at
Polaris BBS for details on it's release.


Downloads:     I will implement code for xprzmodem.library, thus,
               allowing true batch downloads.
               (Almost finished this function)

Hydra:         Online hydra.  Let users upload/download/chat
               simultaneously.
               (Almost finished this function too, Opens it's windows on
                MAXs screen too :) )

SModem:        Aint even tried it yet.  But rest assured, it'll be in
               the commercial version!


List:          Totally new revision of SPin List.  Full utilisation of
               the screen, no matter what lines per screen setting.
               Right now I'm looking into cursor flagging for any
               lines per screen setting. Low memory usage. Custom tag
               lines, (different "Uploaded by..." for each user).
               Dynamic linkage to other doors. Thus, allowing users to
               transfer files whilst in a file list, then continue
               listing.  Sysops will be able to nuke files within a
               file list.

Nuke:          A file deleter similar to Ami-Express's Boss Nuke. Which
               deletes/gives users multiple creds for their uploads, as
               well as returning creds to downloaders of the file (if
               you want to that is)

Messages:      Mini message base which informs users of files they
               uploaded getting nuked/multiple creds.

Tag lists:     Sysops may flag files for deletion, move to another dir,
               make public, etc.

Cursors:       Many of the features will have cursor control to make
               life easier. The main one being Edit-Marked-Files.

Editting:      A new door with a powerful ansi/file_id editor.  This,
               along with a host of other doors will allow your BBS to
               be run totally from remote. 


Thanks to BAnjo for SPin's first util, SPin-Ed, an excellent GUI util for
editting file_id's.. even reads from the tag list and opens up on MAXs
screen.


You have your doubts at such a system existing for MAXs? Well I got this far
in 11 weeks, didnt I?  And it WAS started from scratch.
       ^^ Oops, 13 it is now, took me 2 weeks to do the update.
                ^^ and now 1.3 is out 16 weeks after I started :)
             

That's a brief outlay, but no doubt there'll be a lot more features added. If
